watson.description.config.amount_rows:
Sets amount of rows used for autopage feature
CoreProtect Only
watson.description.config.auto_page: Does automatic 3 pages at a time if enabled
watson.description.config.chat_timeout: The minimum amount of seconds between sent chat messages by the mod
watson.description.config.coreprotect_me:
Disables CoreProtect lookup messages
This will disable the spam from auto pages.
watson.description.config.displayed: If true, watson will draw stuff
watson.description.config.grouping_ores_: Ores are grouped even in creative
watson.description.config.highlight:
What gets highlighted in chat
All entries should have this order: <style><color>;<text>
watson.description.config.highlight_case: If enabled, the highlight patterns will be case sensitive
watson.description.config.highlight_soun:
Set the highlight sound with a sound event key
As example entity.cat.hiss and block.anvil.break
More sound events to be found at:
https://www.digminecraft.com/lists/sound_list_pc.php
Enables making sound when something gets highlight.
Sets the volume that the highlight sound will play.
watson.description.config.linked_creatio: If true, block creations will be linked by vectors
watson.description.config.linked_descrip: If true, block destruction will be linked by vectors
watson.description.config.logblock_messa:
Disables LogBlock lookup messages
This will disable the spam.
watson.description.config.max_auto_pages: Amount of pages that is allowed when auto page is enabled
Amount of automatic stepped thru pages
watson.description.config.only_ore_block: Only shows block in block space
watson.description.config.ore_linewidth: Uses this linewidth for all ores if oreOutlineThicker is enabled
watson.description.config.ore_outline_th:
Ore outline thicker when enabled
If false, uses the integer for outline in watson blocks list config
Default line width: 1
watson.description.config.outline_shown: If true, wireframe outline will be displayed
watson.description.config.page_lines: Number of chat lines in a page
watson.description.config.plugin: Which plugin does the server use
watson.description.config.post_count: Number of edits to be run post
watson.description.config.pre_count: Number of edits to be fetched
watson.description.config.prism_messages:
Disables Prism lookup messages
This will disable the spam.
watson.description.config.reformat_query: Format query in chat more compact if enabled
watson.description.config.region_info_ti: Sets the timeout in seconds when right clicking with a wooden sword
watson.description.config.selection_show: If enabled selection will be shown
watson.description.config.smaller_render: Blocks will have a smaller rendering box
watson.description.config.ss_player_dire: Subdirectory named after the currently selected player is created to hold screenshots of his edits if enabled
watson.description.config.ss_player_suff: Name of current selected player is appended to screenshot files
watson.description.config.teleport_comma:
Sets teleport command
The different format to use inside the placeholders are:
i for integer or d for decimal numbers
Placeholders to use are:
{x:format}, {y:format}, {z:format}, {world}
watson.description.config.time_ordered_d:
If true, ore deposits should be numeric labeled when mined
When false it gets ordered in descending order of rareness of the ore
watson.description.config.use_chat_highl: If true, chat highlighter will be enabled
watson.description.config.watson_prefix: The start of all Watson commands, without a slash
watson.description.hotkey.keybind_comman:
Executes /co i
(Set Plugin in Generic to CoreProtect and only works with CoreProtect)
watson.description.hotkey.keybind_query_:
Query edits after
(Set Plugin in Generic to LogBlock and only works with LogBlock)

Query edits before
(Set Plugin in Generic to LogBlock and only works with LogBlock)
